# MCP + ChatGPT + Cloud Integrations

TrailVerse distributes AI park data through **three surfaces** that share one Express backend:

| Surface | User entry | Protocol | Hosted service |
|---------|------------|----------|----------------|
| **Website Trailie** | `/plan-ai` | REST + WebSocket voice | Next.js + Express on Vercel/Render |
| **ChatGPT App** | ChatGPT App Directory | OpenAI Apps SDK (MCP over HTTP) | `mcp-server/` on Render |
| **Claude** | `/mcp` install guide | MCP connector URL | Same `mcp-server/` on Render |

The Python MCP server is a **thin adapter** — no duplicate business logic. All data flows through `trailverse.onrender.com` (Express).

---

## Cloud deployment (Render)

### MCP server (this repo: `mcp-server/`)

| Item | Value |
|------|--------|
| **Production URL** | `https://trailverse-mcp.onrender.com` |
| **MCP endpoint** | `https://trailverse-mcp.onrender.com/mcp` |
| **Health** | `GET /health` → `{"status":"ok","service":"trailverse-mcp"}` |
| **Blueprint** | `mcp-server/render.yaml` |
| **Runtime** | Python 3.12.7, Uvicorn, FastMCP |
| **Start** | `python -m server.main` |
| **Region** | Oregon (near main backend) |

### Main Express backend

| Item | Value |
|------|--------|
| **API** | `https://trailverse.onrender.com/api` |
| **Used by MCP** | `TRAILVERSE_API_BASE` env on MCP service |

### Required paired secret (production)

Both services must set the **same** `MCP_BYPASS_KEY`:

1. **MCP server** (`mcp-server/server/client.py`) sends header `X-TrailVerse-MCP-Key` on every backend request
2. **Express** (`server/src/middleware/mcpBypass.js`) sets `req.skipAnonymousRateLimit = true` when header matches

Without this, all ChatGPT/Claude traffic shares one IP and hits the **60 req / 15 min** anonymous API limit immediately.

Generate: `python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(48))"`

