## The 5 MCP tools

All **read-only** (`readOnlyHint: true`). Registered in `mcp-server/server/main.py`.

| Tool | Purpose | Primary backend calls |
|------|---------|------------------------|
| `plan_trip` | AI itinerary (any US destination) | `POST /api/ai/chat-anonymous` |
| `get_park_details` | Live park card (470+ NPS sites) | `GET /api/parks/:code/details` + alerts, weather, campgrounds, permits, feed |
| `compare_parks` | 2–4 park comparison | `POST /api/parks/compare`, `/compare/summary` |
| `search_parks` | Find parks by name/state/activity | `GET /api/parks/search` |
| `find_events` | Ranger programs | `GET /api/events` |

### Tool output shape (dual format)

Every tool returns:

1. **`structuredContent`** — JSON for ChatGPT **inline HTML widgets**
2. **`text`** — Markdown for Claude and LLMs without widget UI
3. Optional **images** — SSRF-safe fetch (nps.gov, unsplash, wikimedia) via Pillow

Formatters: `mcp-server/server/formatters.py`  
Pydantic inputs: `mcp-server/server/types.py` (flat schemas for OpenAI compatibility)

### Anonymous AI limits

- Website anonymous chat: 5 messages / 48h per IP (funnels signups)
- MCP uses same anonymous endpoint intentionally (OpenAI review needs no demo account)
- MCP bypass lifts **Express** rate limit only; MCP has its own `rate_limit.py` caps

### Multi-turn planning

`mcp-server/server/conversations.py` — in-memory session store for follow-ups ("add day 4"). Lost on server restart (acceptable for thin adapter).

