## MCP environment variables

From `mcp-server/.env.example` and `render.yaml`:

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `TRAILVERSE_API_BASE` | Express backend root (no `/api` suffix in env; client adds paths) |
| `MCP_SERVER_BASE` | Public URL for widget resource URIs |
| `TRAILVERSE_WEB_BASE` | Website for CTA links in widgets |
| `MCP_BYPASS_KEY` | **Secret** — must match Express |
| `BACKEND_TIMEOUT` | Default 120s (plan_trip can be slow) |
| `MCP_PLAN_TRIP_LIMIT` / `MCP_PLAN_TRIP_WINDOW` | MCP-side fuse for AI calls |
| `MCP_READ_LIMIT` / `MCP_READ_WINDOW` | MCP-side fuse for read tools |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | Python logging |

Local dev:

```bash
cd mcp-server && python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
export TRAILVERSE_API_BASE=http://localhost:5001
python -m server.main   # → http://localhost:8000/mcp
```

ChatGPT dev test: ngrok `8000` → paste `https://….ngrok.app/mcp` in ChatGPT developer connector settings.

